Prerequisites:
    - python 3
    - pytorch
    - pytorch geometric
    - pytorch lightning
    - rdkit
    - numpy
    - networkx

Train on synthetic random graphs, specifying a graph family and parameters:
    - binomial graphs, on 4 gpus, with parameter p in (0.4, 0.6):
        python graphae/syntetic_graphs/main.py --progress_bar -i 1 -g 4 --graph_family binomial -b 64 --p_min 0.4 --p_max 0.6
    - mix of 10 different graphs families, on 4 gpus, with parameter p in (0.4, 0.6):
        python graphae/syntetic_graphs/main.py --progress_bar -i 1 -g 4 --graph_family all -b 64

Train on molecular graphs from QM9:
    - download the qm9 dataset (http://quantum-machine.org/datasets/) and run the suffle_and_filter_qm9_sdf function
      in graphae/molecular_graphs/utils to extract a shuffled sdf file with only rdkit-readable molecules and run:

        python graphae/molecular_graphs/main.py --progress_bar -i 1 -g 4 -b 16


